  <Instrument_Host>
    <name>DCAM3 (Deployable Camera 3)</name>
    <type>Spacecraft</type>
    <naif_host_id>-37500</naif_host_id>
    <description>The Deployable Camera 3 (DCAM3) is a compact camera system designed for simultaneous close-range observations of impact events using the Small Carry-on Impactor (SCI). It includes an analog camera (DCAM3-A), a digital camera (DCAM3-D), a power unit, and antennas for transmissions. The cameras are supported by receiver units and a control unit on the Hayabusa2 spacecraft. DCAM3 is the successor to DCAM1 and DCAM2, which were used for monitoring the deployment of JAXA's solar sail on the IKAROS spacecraft.</description>
